{"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/variant_dict_ptr-6dgor"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/contains(key:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/end()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/init_(from:)-2u3tj","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/init_(from:)-5rs48","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/insertValue(key:value:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/lookupValue(key:expectedType:)-7v6kw","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/lookupValue(key:expectedType:)-9lxae","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/ref()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/remove(key:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDictProtocol\/unref()"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Protocol","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19VariantDictProtocolP","title":"VariantDictProtocol","symbolKind":"protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VariantDictProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantDictProtocol"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantDictProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can be used for doing a sequence of dictionary lookups in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"efficient way on an existing "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" dictionary or it can be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to construct new dictionaries with a hashtable-like interface.  It"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can also be used for taking existing dictionaries and modifying them","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in order to create new ones."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict"},{"type":"text","text":" can only be used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARDICT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dictionaries."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" allocated on the stack or on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"heap.  When using a stack-allocated "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict","isActive":true},{"text":", you begin with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_init()"},{"text":" and free the resources with a call to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_variant_dict_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Heap-allocated "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict"},{"type":"text","text":" follows normal refcounting rules: you"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allocate it with "},{"code":"g_variant_dict_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_dict_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"code":"g_variant_dict_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_end()"},{"type":"text","text":" is used to convert the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict","type":"reference"},{"text":" back into a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dictionary-type "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":".  When used with stack-allocated instances,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this also implicitly frees all associated memory, but for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"heap-allocated instances, you must still call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_unref()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"afterwards.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will typically want to use a heap-allocated ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantDict","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you expose it as part of an API.  For most other uses, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stack-allocated form will be more convenient."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider the following two examples that do the same thing in each","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"style: take an existing dictionary and look up the “count” uint32","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"key, adding 1 to it if it is found, or returning an error if the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"key is not found.  Each returns the new dictionary as a floating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Using-a-stack-allocated-GVariantDict","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Using a stack-allocated GVariantDict"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["  GVariant *","  add_to_count (GVariant  *orig,","                GError   **error)","  {","    GVariantDict dict;","    guint32 count;","","    g_variant_dict_init (&dict, orig);","    if (!g_variant_dict_lookup (&dict, \"count\", \"u\", &count))","      {","        g_set_error (...);","        g_variant_dict_clear (&dict);","        return NULL;","      }","","    g_variant_dict_insert (&dict, \"count\", \"u\", count + 1);","","    return g_variant_dict_end (&dict);","  }"]},{"text":"Using heap-allocated GVariantDict","anchor":"Using-heap-allocated-GVariantDict","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["  GVariant *","  add_to_count (GVariant  *orig,","                GError   **error)","  {","    GVariantDict *dict;","    GVariant *result;","    guint32 count;","","    dict = g_variant_dict_new (orig);","","    if (g_variant_dict_lookup (dict, \"count\", \"u\", &count))","      {","        g_variant_dict_insert (dict, \"count\", \"u\", count + 1);","        result = g_variant_dict_end (dict);","      }","    else","      {","        g_set_error (...);","        result = NULL;","      }","","    g_variant_dict_unref (dict);","","    return result;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier